rist's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":18,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705192,"age":31,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":40,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Thomas Richmond was born in England. She married Thomas Richmond before 1316, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–1316":"–1316","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1453":"1453","before 1316":"enne 1316","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","England":"England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–1316":"–1316","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1453":"1453","before 1316":"ennen vuotta 1316","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","England":"England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","–1316":"–1316","–Male":"Dé